passages.text: USA | Cosmetics, Household & Personal Care
Model Update: Q2 In Liner Consumer Cautious;Strategic Initiatives Unlerway

Q2 sales and EPS were within range of cons. Sales were +1.5% Y/Y and at the high end of guide, led by a strong semi-annual sale. FY guide was narrowed,while Q3 EPS was below cons. Tariff impacts will hit hardest in Q3, but mgmt is confident it can improve mitigation offsets over time. Co intends to ramp up digital upgrades and packaging/labeling in the fall, with new customer acquisition a key oppty. Model adj. for updated guidance and PT raised to $32.

**Q2** **Results** **vs.** **Expectations:** Overall sales of $1.55B (+1.5% Y/Y) were in line w/ consensus and near high end of guide. U.S. & Canada store sales +5% Y/Y, International -3% Y/Y, and e-com -10%.GM% of 41.3% was +10bps vs. estimates and +30bps Y/Y. SG&A of $483M was +215bps Y/Y as a % of sales and above cons ests at $463M. Op Income of $172M and OM% of 11.1% were below ests for $175M and 11.3%, resp. Q2 Adj-EPS of $0.37 was in range of consensus at $0.38 and near the high end of guidance for $0.33-$$0.38.

**Consumer Trends:** Customers displayed caution and value-seeking behavior, and more intentional purchasing patterns, in Q2. Consumers were selective w/ spending and prioritized purchases that support well-being and convenience. Dual-channel traffic was positive in Q2, with store traffic above co's third-party benchmarks, but below Q1 levels, reflecting moderating consumer trends.

**Progress on Strategic Initiatives:** Co further detailed its strategic initiatives under new CEO Daniel Heaf, starting with upgrades across digital platforms in Sept to improve functionality, product imagery, and storytelling. This includes a new app with a mobile web relaunch in October. Heaf noted co is underutilizing 1000s of ft of window space in off-mall locations and will use it to enhance brand storytelling. To improve packaging and labeling, co intends to highlight 48-hr hydration on body lotions, emphasize stress relief and sleep benefits for aromatherapy products,and increase messaging for dermatologist-tested products. Packaging upgrades, esp in candles,are solid, though some reviews express the view that the design upgrade does not justify the almost 50% price markup. Heaf stressed that co's biggest oppty to drive durable growth is new customer acquisition, esp younger consumers, which will be supported by expanding disty with third parties and internationally. We're encouraged by co's updated initiatives and efforts to reduce promos and lean on product marketing/Storytelling to drive AUR growth.

**Tariff Update:** BBWI expects a ~$85M net impact from tariff headwinds for FY25, with a 240bps headwind in Q3 and 100bps impact in Q4. Disproportionate pressure in Q3 stems from inventory receipts in April and May when China rates were 145%. However, mgmt. is confident it can further mitigate tariff costs over time via supply chain optimization, targeted assortment changes, and strategic pricing.
**Model Update:** We model Q3 and FY25 in line with guidance. PT higher to $32 based on ~9x FY26E

Our Hold rating is driven by our view that BBWI is positioned unfavorably in the current macro environment, as we see consumers trading out of the brand into mass alternatives. Adjacent categories have not offered incremental market share we had hoped for, and the BBWI consumer seems uncomfortable with the higher price points. Our expectation is that promotion will continue at current levels, holding profit margins at mid- teens+.

- Op margins stable  
- Promotional levels stabilize

- EBITDA growth flat to -LSD%  
- PT = \(\) 20\(based on \sim 6x reduced FY26E EPS\)

Top Material Issue(s): (1) Energy Management: It is becoming increasingly important for companies to manage their overall energy efficiency, and their access to alternative energy sources. Efficiency in this area can have financial implications through direct cost savings. (2) Product Design & Lifecycle Management: Companies that effectively manage the sustainability of packaging & sourcing of materials may be better positioned to capture shifting consumer demand and avoid regulation related to producer responsibility.

Company Target(s): (1) Reduce Scope 1 and 2 emissions 50% and shift packaging to be 100% reusable, recyclable or compostable by 2030. (2) Create products with more sustainable ingredients and give customers more informed product choices with additional transparency on inputs and manufacturing processes.
Qs to Mgmt: (1) Does formulating products with a lower environmental footprint create pressure on the supply chain? (2) What is the impact on margins of increased recycling efforts?
ESG Sector Deep Dive: Multiline Retail

- Back to school & related demand among Gen Z  
- Holiday 2024  
- ESG: Brand & strategy development that aligns with investor priorities re: impact

FY25 Guide Narrowed; FY25 In Line with Street; Q3 ES Below: Mgmt. arrowed its FY25 sales guide to \(+1.5\%\) to \(+2.7\%\) from \(+1\%\) to \(+3\%\) , compared to \(0.5\%\) at \(+2.2\%\) . EPS guidance was raised to \(\) 3.35\(\)3.60 from \(\) 3.25 - \(\) 3.60\(, in line with cons. of\) \ \(3.48\) at the midpoint. 3Q25 outlook for sales of \(+1\%\) to \(+3\%\) vs. \(+1.9\%\) cons. EPS of \(\) 0.37 - \(\) 0.45\(becomensus ests. at\) \ \(0.49\) . FY guide reflects net tariff impact and removal of Canadian retaliatory tariffs starting Sept 1.

Bath & Body Works is a beauty and personal care brand with a focus on fragrance & body care, and operates over 1,700 stores.

We value BBW using a forward P/E multiple. Key risks include macroeconomic conditions, retail traffic, promotions & discounts affecting margins, sourcing & input cost fluctuation, staffing & retention, loss of key personnel, and competition.
